Articles.Content: recently in career mode building ship with this size tank and noticed I could not attach any engine to the bottom of the tank, tried multiple reloads and reboots. No dice. But could use smaller tanks in its place stacked.
Try holding down the ALT button (modifier key) while trying to place the engine.  Holding down ALT forces the part to attach to the node, instead of trying to surface attach.

That was one of the first things I did to no avail.I think there's a bug. I also have this issue with other parts attaching to end of cargo bay doors. You can attach to the parts but  it's only via the node on the opposite end of the part you are placing. and it will put it inside the either tank or cargo bay with or without you pressing the alt key.

Well, to dig a little deeper-

What mods are you using?

Which platform? (Windows, Mac, Linux)

Latest version, 1.0.5?

A screenshot may be helpful.

Also, if you are using sub-assemblies or merging ship files, this sometimes causes nodes to disappear.  Anything you can do to narrow down the problem may be helpful.  I tried a basic vessel in the VAB, with a command pod, the fuel tank, and finally an engine on the bottom.  Does this simple arrangement work properly?  

Edited February 18, 2016 by RexKramer

No, Mods,

Windows

Latest Version Automatic Updates from Steam

will provide screen shots when I get home.

I can see the nodes, it just wouldn't attach.

I'll attempt that when I get home, but when I was experiencing this, I had loaded up my Duna ship I was creating the night before, attached an decoupler, then the tank in question, went to put the engine on and no attach.
Yes, a picture and/or craft file (up to the point of engine attach) would help.

only one that attaches properly
